{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10",
    "summary": "Source text for Ecclesiastes 10 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:1",
      "text": "Dead flies cause the ointment of the apothecary to send forth a stinking savour: so doth a little folly him that is in reputation for wisdom and honour.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:2",
      "text": "A wise man’s heart is at his right hand; but a fool’s heart at his left.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:3",
      "text": "Yea also, when he that is a fool walketh by the way, his wisdom faileth him, and he saith to every one that he is a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:4",
      "text": "If the spirit of the ruler rise up against thee, leave not thy place; for yielding pacifieth great offences.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:5",
      "text": "There is an evil which I have seen under the sun, as an error which proceedeth from the ruler:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:6",
      "text": "Folly is set in great dignity, and the rich sit in low place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:7",
      "text": "I have seen servants upon horses, and princes walking as servants upon the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:8",
      "text": "He that diggeth a pit shall fall into it; and whoso breaketh an hedge, a serpent shall bite him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:9",
      "text": "Whoso removeth stones shall be hurt therewith; and he that cleaveth wood shall be endangered thereby.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:10",
      "text": "If the iron be blunt, and he do not whet the edge, then must he put to more strength: but wisdom is profitable to direct.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:11",
      "text": "Surely the serpent will bite without enchantment; and a babbler is no better.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:12",
      "text": "The words of a wise man’s mouth are gracious; but the lips of a fool will swallow up himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:13",
      "text": "The beginning of the words of his mouth is foolishness: and the end of his talk is mischievous madness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:14",
      "text": "A fool also is full of words: a man cannot tell what shall be; and what shall be after him, who can tell him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:15",
      "text": "The labour of the foolish wearieth every one of them, because he knoweth not how to go to the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:16",
      "text": "Woe to thee, O land, when thy king is a child, and thy princes eat in the morning!",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:17",
      "text": "Blessed art thou, O land, when thy king is the son of nobles, and thy princes eat in due season, for strength, and not for drunkenness!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:18",
      "text": "By much slothfulness the building decayeth; and through idleness of the hands the house droppeth through.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:19",
      "text": "A feast is made for laughter, and wine maketh merry: but money answereth all things.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.10.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:20",
      "text": "Curse not the king, no not in thy thought; and curse not the rich in thy bedchamber: for a bird of the air shall carry the voice, and that which hath wings shall tell the matter.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    }
  ]
}
